metadata.name: Mood hunt
metadata.description:
As I wandered through forest thickets, steep mountain trails, and the dark city streets, I tracked sentiment.

I pricked up my ears and scrutinized the silhouettes and shadows of the darkness. I let my claws out and lurked, not letting the faces fool me even in the light of day. My intuition led me on the trail of what would light my inner fire, what would be my Mood...



Digital oil handmade
4134 x 5315 pixels
